    <h3 class="mt-5">📊 Logical Data Model</h3>
    <p>
        This data model captures the structure of EventNest and how entities relate.
        It demonstrates two key one-to-many relationships:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Event → Booking</strong>: One event can have multiple ticket bookings</li>
        <li><strong>Event → Review</strong>: One event can have multiple user reviews</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The main entities and attributes include:</p>

    <h5 class="mt-3">🗂 Event</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Id (PK)</strong> – Unique event ID</li>
        <li>Title – Name of the event</li>
        <li>Date – Scheduled date</li>
        <li>City – City where the event happens</li>
        <li>Venue – Event venue</li>
        <li>Category – Movie, Play, Sports, etc.</li>
        <li>Price – Ticket price</li>
        <li>PosterUrl – Image link for the event</li>
    </ul>

    <h5 class="mt-3">🎟 Booking</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Id (PK)</strong> – Unique booking ID</li>
        <li><strong>EventId (FK)</strong> – Related event</li>
        <li>UserName – User who booked</li>
        <li>TicketCount – Number of seats booked</li>
        <li>BookingDate – Date of booking</li>
    </ul>

    <h5 class="mt-3">⭐ Review</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Id (PK)</strong> – Unique review ID</li>
        <li><strong>EventId (FK)</strong> – Related event</li>
        <li>UserName – Reviewer’s name</li>
        <li>Rating – 1 to 5 stars</li>
        <li>Comment – Text feedback</li>
    </ul>

